[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dominic Ball: Peterborough United sign Rotherham United defender on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Peterborough United have signed defender Dominic Ball on loan from Rotherham until the end of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 21-year-old has appeared 13 times for the Championship side since joining them for an undisclosed fee from Tottenham Hotspur last summer.
He previously had loans at Cambridge and Rangers, whom he helped win promotion to the Scottish Premiership and lift the Challenge Cup last term.
Ball joins a side two points off the League One play-off places.
